<h1><strong><span style="color: rgb(184, 49, 47);">Overview</span></strong></h1>

<p>In this job, you will be presented with headlines and opinion articles from the Canadian newspaper &nbsp;The Globe and Mail, and real comments that people posted in response to these articles.&nbsp;</p>

<p>Your job is to&nbsp;</p>

<ol>
	<li>read the opinion article;&nbsp;</li>
	<li>read the corresponding comment; and&nbsp;</li>
	<li>answer the presented questions related to <strong>constructiveness</strong>&nbsp; of these comments using your intuitions and the guidelines provided below.&nbsp;</li>
</ol>

<p>If you are curious, we are interested in building computational systems to organize news comments in a meaningful way and your annotations will be used in building and evaluating such systems.&nbsp;</p>

<h1><span style="color: rgb(184, 49, 47);">Guidelines</span></h1>

<p>A <em>constructive</em> comment is one which exchanges intelligent and informed remarks that are relevant to the article. Below we point out some characteristics of constructive and non-constructive comments.&nbsp;</p>

